Paper: hep-th/0210101

Date: 2002-10-10

Title: Rolling Tachyons in String Cosmology

Authors: Chanju Kim (Ewha W.U.), Hang Bae Kim (Lausanne U.), Yoonbai Kim

(Sungkyunkwan U.)Comments: More references added. A version to be published in Phys.Lett.B

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B552 (2003) 111-118

We study the role of rolling tachyons in the cosmological model withdilatonic gravity. In the string frame, flat space solutions of bothinitial-stage and late-time are obtained in closed form. In the Einstein frame,we show that every expanding solution is decelerating.